    <svcsection id="S12019" division="truck" date="07/28/2006">
        <title>RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - MXT</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>MXT</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The International&#174; medium duty truck line uses a high life cycle, low maintenance cooling
                    system, with vehicle down time anticipation at an industry low. The design eliminates long periods
                    of down time waiting for radiator cooling component repair. Figures 1 and 2 show various Cooling
                    Module components.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Protect all open ports in the charge air system during removal and installation. Dirt or
                            foreign particles in charge air cooling piping or cooling system components could cause
                            internal damage to engine parts.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="f1201901" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg12/g1201901.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                             scalefitheight="472px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Radiator View from Top Driver Side</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f1201902" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg12/g1201902.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                             scalefitheight="472px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. Radiator View from Lower Passenger Side</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The Radiator Assembly (from Modine) consists of the Radiator Core, AC Condenser, Charge
                            Air Cooler, Radiator Frame and Recirculation Seal, Fan Shroud, Radiator Side-Mounting
                            Brackets, and Radiator Mounting Blocks and Brackets.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Please refer to the Torque Tables in this manual for specific torque requirements.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
